                        <item xml:id="e1">- A devotional image of European origin is sewn on fol. 4v.&#xD;
- The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting: fols. 9rb-10ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters written interlineally in the main hand: e.g., fols. 15vb, 47va, 70ra, 97rb.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally in small script in a secondary hand: fols. 11va, 12rb.&#xD;
- Omitted letters added at the end of the line in a recent secondary hand in blue pen: fols. 104va, 106ra.&#xD;
- Correction written over erasures in the main hand: fol. 91vb.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., fols. 10rb, 14vb, 17va, 35rb.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with thin red lines:  fols. 44va, 67rb, 87ra, 94ra.&#xD;
- Lacunae (spaces for rubricated names left unfilled) on many leaves: e.g., fols. 21vb, 26rb, 29vb, 42ra, 70vb, 92vb, 106va.</item>
                     </list>
